etType":"tracksetAuto","coordinates":[53.9706172,-122.8754255],"distance":52607.495994250785,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":16.81,"percent":31.944356044400777},{"id":"intermediate","distance":23.67,"percent":44.9847231792245},{"id":"advanced","distance":12.14,"percent":23.070920776374653}],"links":{"website":{"en":"http://caledonianordic.com"},"weather":{"en":"https://www.wunderground.com/dashboard/pws/IBCPRINC3"},"webcam":{"en":"https://caledonianordic.com/webcam-gallery/"}},"snow24h":6,"snowAnnual":5,"currentTemp":7,"currentCond":"no snow","waxKick":"kickwax","waxGlide":"glidewax","elevation":610,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2026-03-06T22:04:27.856Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-7","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:57.082Z","clubId":"BC-CaledoniaNordic","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>14 April 2026 Tuesday 12:01 PM\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2>\u003Cstrong>The Ballad of Winter's Last Stand\u003C/strong>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Our Monday tears for Winter Four\u003Cbr>Had scarcely left the air,\u003Cbr>When Tuesday's sober scouting party\u003Cbr>Confirmed she'd left her lair.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The grooming crew, by duty bound&mdash;\u003Cbr>Though aided, it is said,\u003Cbr>By cappuccinos, rich and rare,\u003Cbr>With lavish foamy head&mdash;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Set forth to tour the winding trails,\u003Cbr>To see what still remained,\u003Cbr>And found that Spring had moved right in\u003Cbr>Before she'd even knocked or phoned.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>They found some ice&mdash;spectacular stuff&mdash;\u003Cbr>All polished, hard and fast;\u003Cbr>The sort that lets your entire life\u003Cbr>Flash brightly as you pass.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>They found bare dirt in growing bands,\u003Cbr>Where skis looked rather grim.\u003Cbr>The forest whispered, \"Not today...\"\u003Cbr>Then added, \"Portage, friend.\"\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>They found the mud in generous pools,\u003Cbr>Soft offerings, dark and deep,\u003Cbr>Prepared to claim abandoned skis\u003Cbr>The swamp gods long to keep.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Now none of this will halt the few\u003Cbr>Who'll venture out regardless.\u003Cbr>We tip our hats to such resolve...\u003Cbr>While gently questioning the thought process.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The season now becomes a place\u003Cbr>Where every tribe appears;\u003Cbr>A glorious muddled free-for-all\u003Cbr>That marks the changing years.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The skiers still will soldier on\u003Cbr>Till grass outnumbers snow,\u003Cbr>Insisting every brownish patch\u003Cbr>\"Has one more lap to go.\"\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The dogs, meanwhile, will materialize\u003Cbr>In places unforeseen.\u003Cbr>Kind owners, please remove the proof\u003Cbr>Your faithful friends have been.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The fat bikers, those fearless souls,\u003Cbr>Who scoff at mud and slush,\u003Cbr>Will happily investigate\u003Cbr>What others wouldn't touch.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The runners and the walkers, too,\u003Cbr>Are kindly asked to tread\u003Cbr>The singletrack where possible&mdash;\u003Cbr>Leave postholes for the dead.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The lodge will close at half-past four;\u003Cbr>The washrooms need a rest.\u003Cbr>Even faithful buildings earn\u003Cbr>An early springtime recess.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Disc golfers, yes, we know you're keen,\u003Cbr>Your baskets call your name.\u003Cbr>But patience&mdash;soon enough you'll fling\u003Cbr>Your plastic discs again.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>So here's to trails that can't decide\u003Cbr>If winter's gone for good;\u003Cbr>Where every outing is a guess,\u003Cbr>Yet still feels as it should.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>If Aaron's vanished down the trails,\u003Cbr>Pursuing jobs eighteen,\u003Cbr>The yellow safe outside the office\u003Cbr>Will gladly intervene.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>A little gift helps keep these woods\u003Cbr>In shape for all who roam;\u003Cbr>And rentals, too, have earned relief&mdash;\u003Cbr>Our gear is heading home.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>So shoulder hope and common sense,\u003Cbr>Bring laughter if you can.\u003Cbr>We'll stumble into spring together...\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Exactly as we always planned.\u003C/p>"},"account":"6359992aa29dbd647df018b2","author":"SnowScribe","timestamp":"2026-04-14T19:01:00.000Z"},"reportNotices":[{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.228Z","clubId":"BC-CaledoniaNordic","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>CNSC's WEATHER STATIONS:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.wunderground.com/dashboard/pws/IBCPRINC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Air temp - South side of the Stadium\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.wunderground.com/dashboard/pws/IPRINC46\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Air temp - trail from Lot #2 to Picadilly Circus\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.wunderground.com/dashboard/pws/IPRINC47\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Snow temp - trail from Lot #2&nbsp; to Picadilly Circus\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>.\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch4>\u003Cstrong>WEATHER GUESSES:\u003C/strong>\u003C/h4>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://weather.gc.ca/en/location/index.html?coords=53.912,-122.776\">Environment Canada\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.theweathernetwork.com/ca/weather/british-columbia/prince-george\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Weather Network\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.accuweather.com/en/ca/prince-george/v2m/weather-forecast/47164\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Accuweather\u003C/a>&nbsp;\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.theweather.net/prince-george.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Weather Net\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003Ca href=\"https://weather.com/weather/tenday/l/Prince+George+British+Columbia+Canada?canonicalCityId=a35a215844080235c426c61216e7dccdbc8c23c2f02e54e812432b635ce60942\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Weather Channel\u003C/a>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>"},"timestamp":"2026-03-15T07:00:00.000Z"},{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.228Z","clubId":"BC-CaledoniaNordic","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>TRAIL CLOSURE NOTICE #1\u003C/strong>: The following trails have sung their final note:&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Up the Creek\u003C/strong>&nbsp;(past Old Biathlon Loop),&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Hickory Wing\u003C/strong>,&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Cranbrook Climb\u003C/strong>&nbsp;(uphill from Northern Crossing),&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Old SawMill Loop\u003C/strong>,&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Lynx\u003C/strong>,&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Raven&rsquo;s Col\u003C/strong>,&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Birch Bend\u003C/strong>,&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Ridge Runner\u003C/strong>, &amp; alas, the flooding&nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Moon Dog\u003C/strong>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv>\u003Cstrong>.\u003C/strong>\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\u003Cstrong>TRAIL CLOSURE NOTICE #2\u003C/strong>: The Lower (east) portion of \u003Cstrong>DogOnIt\u003C/strong> is closed for the rest of this season, as Terus is excavating a portion of it for their gravel operation. &nbsp;&nbsp;They are also doing work in the cleared area between \u003Cstrong>K-9 Intersection &amp; Sundog/TopDog intersection\u003C/strong>, so that is also closed &amp; signed appropriately. &nbsp;\u003Cstrong>Underdog\u003C/strong> still connects to \u003Cstrong>Upper Dogonit\u003C/strong> for a Loop, and \u003Cstrong>Top Dog\u003C/strong> connects to \u003Cstrong>Sun Dog\u003C/strong>, for a longer return loop. \u003Cem>&nbsp;\u003C/em>