T20:02:37.036Z","clubId":"US-WA-Spokane","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Hello Mount Spokane State Park Nordic Community,\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>As you may have guessed, barring significant additional snowfall, our Nordic grooming season has come to an end. The recent warm temperatures and rapidly melting snow has made continued grooming problematic. Hats off to our fabulous grooming team of Captain Ginge, Juan Grande, and Husky Dave for their wonderful work in challenging conditions this year. We are fortunate to have such talented groomers as part of our State Parks team.\u003Cbr />\u003Cbr />Thank you also goes out to our valiant volunteer groomers who tended to the trails when there was insufficient snow for our big machines. The early part of the season was only made possible by their efforts.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Thanks also to the Spokane Nordic Ski Association for all the work they put into supporting and growing this tremendous sport. Hundreds of volunteer hours are contributed each year to make the Mount Spokane Nordic Ski Area the special place that it is. Your efforts are appreciated.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Finally, thank you to our park visitors. Despite weak snowfall and dubious weather conditions, you continued to show up to enjoy the trails. It is our pleasure to try and consistently provide the best possible skiing conditions that we can possibly produce, and we can't wait until next winter.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Happy Trails,\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Rex Schultz\u003Cbr />Inland Northwest Community Engagement Manager \u003Cbr />Washington State Parks\u003C/p>\n\n"},"account":"6986159c6b94c8f10b447e40","author":"T-Rex","timestamp":"2026-03-25T19:16:47.000Z","deviceId":"D36A7AE3-B278-428E-9D06-2E23CD3EDBB1"}},{"clubId":"ON-Kanata","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"CA","regionId":"ON","permalink":"Kanata-Nordic","bounds":[[-75.8726648,45.328192],[-75.8509773,45.3408697]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca582"],"name":{"en":"Kanata Nordic"},"nameS":{"en":"Kanata"},"city":{"en":"Kanata"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>Kanata Nordic Ski Club offers groomed ski and snowshoe trails, children's and adult learn-to-ski and racing programs, events and loppets to its members. Located on the Wesley Clover Parks lands, Kanata Nordic has a cabin with wood stove at its campground trail (411 Corkstown) and large tent at its equestrian trail head (401 Corkstown). Please consult&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https://www.kanatanordic.ca/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://www.kanatanordic.ca\u003C/a>&nbsp;for more details about memberships, programs, renting ski equipment, and events. Non-members can only ski or snowshoe the Kanata Nordic trails if&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https://www.paypal.com/webapps/hermes?token=8U017763GU943331C&amp;useraction=commit&amp;wpsFlowRedirectToXorouterSkipHermesStartTime=1708354529010&amp;flowType=WPS&amp;mfid=1708354528817_f283464fb1473\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">they pay for a day pass\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Ontario","country":"Canada","logo":"2024-02-19T10-28-43-695-05:00_ON-Kanata_logo.png","banner":"2024-02-19T10-36-26-088-05:00_ON-Kanata_Finn.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"24h":{"ts":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"12h":{"ts":"2026-03-22T16:44:30.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"}},"lgg":{"14d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":15667.63,"percent":100}],"7d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":15667.63,"percent":100}],"4d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":15667.63,"percent":100}],"36h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":15667.63,"percent":100}],"24h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":15667.63,"percent":100}],"12h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":15667.63,"percent":100}]},"lastGroomedGroups":[{"id":"