k Lodge is situated on 80 stunning acres, surrounded by Stillwater State Forest and perched overlooking Dog Lake. We're a short drive from Whitefish, Glacier National Park, and the Flathead Valley.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cbr>While keeping a private atmosphere for our guests in the summer for their occasions, we open close to 30 kilometers of groomed nordic trail systems in the winter to the public of the Flathead Valley and Northwest Montana. We have a nordic ski shop, full coffee bar/restaurant/bar and offer homemade meals made from locally sourced ingredients including our greenhouse.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>We groom with ATV's on cat tracks with a YTS Ginzu groomer and a Pistenbully 100 Snowcat.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Overnight lodging, events, nordic trails, rentals, food &amp; drink. Come and explore Dog Creek.\u003C/p>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>From Canada, take Highway 93 south of Eureka, Montana for 30.6 miles (Approx 49km) and Dog Creek Lodge will be on your right. Park, check in, and enjoy the trails! From the Flathead Valley (Kalispell, Columbia Falls, Bigfork, Whitefish) Take Hwy 93 North for 20 miles out of Whitefish or (32km) and Dog Creek Lodge will be at the bottom of the hill on your left. Park, check in, enjoy the trails. Fun Fact: If the snow was good and you didn't mind the highway traffic, skiing out to Dog Creek from Whitefish would be around the same km as skiing all of our trails when we are fully open. Come on out and stay a while!&nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"region":"Montana","country":"USA","regions":["US-CCSAA"],"logo":"2025-01-14T13-32-52-520-07:00_US-MT-DogCreekLodge_logo_0.png","banner":"2025-01-14T13-35-28-722-07:00_US-MT-DogCreekLodge_Brett_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-03-16T19:41:24.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-03-16T19:41:24.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-03-16T19:41:24.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026-03-16T19:41:24.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"24h":{"ts":"2026-03-16