 the Eastern Sierra offers unparalleled scenery, serenity, fitness, and \u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"92\">fun for\u003C/span> \u003Cspan data-text-len=\"92\">everyone, from beginners to experts, thanks to its varied terrain and the \u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"92\">stunning backdrop of\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\"> &nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"17\">the&nbsp;Sierra&nbsp;Nevada\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"2\">.&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"67\">Miles of snow-covered roads and play \u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"67\">areas are open to snowmobilers\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"5\">&nbsp;over\u003C/span> \u003Cspan data-text-len=\"18\">snow&nbsp;vehicles&nbsp;(OSV\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">s\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">)\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"25\">, and non-motorized&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"25\">users\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"15\">&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;Mammoth\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"6\">&nbsp;Lakes\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"6\">,&nbsp;June\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"5\">&nbsp;Lake\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"10\">, and Mono&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"12\">Lake&nbsp;areas.&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>&nbsp;\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"77\">The diverse terrain, including wide-open meadows, forested areas, and groomed\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cdiv>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"54\">networks,&nbsp;provides&nbsp;opportunities&nbsp;for&nbsp;all&nbsp;skill&nbsp;levels.\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"6\">&nbsp;The&nbsp;m\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"25\">otorized&nbsp;multi-use&nbsp;trails\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"13\">, marked&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"13\">with&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"84\">orange diamonds, are groomed by the Town of Mammoth Lakes and local commercial guide\u003C/span> \u003Cspan data-text-len=\"10\">services. \u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"76\">There are over 30 miles of groomed non-motorized winter trails in and around \u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"83\">Mammoth Lakes, providing opportunities to explore the Inyo National Forest on skis,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"33\">snowshoes, and winter fat&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"33\">bikes.&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>&nbsp;\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"26\">Beyond the groomed trails,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"32\">&nbsp;there&nbsp;are&nbsp;approximately&nbsp;150,000\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"14\">acres open&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"14\">to \u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"3\">OSV\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">s\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"2\">,&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"11\">Nordic&nbsp;skie\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">r\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"16\">s&nbsp;and&nbsp;snowshoers\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"40\">&nbsp;equipped&nbsp;and&nbsp;prepared&nbsp;to&nbsp;travel&nbsp;off&nbsp;the\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cdiv>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"23\">maintained&nbsp;trail&nbsp;system\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">s\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text-len=\"1\">.\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>"},"region":"California","country":"USA","groups":[{"groupId":"Motorized","groupName":"Motorized Multi-Use Routes","groupBounds":[[-119.06320817832538,37.64949223590808],[-118.89564772306737,37.83084202443975]]},{"groupId":"Obisidian","groupOrder":1,"groupName":"Obsidian Dome Nordic Area","groupBounds":[[-119.03734433654552,37.75591627347577],[-119.01367510651254,37.778884899729654]]},{"groupId":"ShadyRestPark","groupOrder":2,"groupName":"Shady Rest Park","groupBounds":[[-118.96899798991507,37.6471672862371],[-118.94961684932979,37.65456735969071]]},{"groupId":"Sherwin","groupOrder":3,"groupName":"Sherwin Winter Trails","groupBounds":[[-118.97640639642265,37.620722119011276],[-118.96258946048832,37.62997211784845]]}],"logo":"2024-12-19T21-28-07-464-07:00_US-CA-Mammoth_logo_0.png","banner":"2024-12-13T14-26-54-582-07:00_US-CA-Mammoth_Rob_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-03-06T05:31:56.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-03-06T05:31:56.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-03-06T05:31:56.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026-03-06T05:31:56.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"24h":{"ts":"2026-03-06T05:31:56.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"12h":{"ts":"2026-03-06T05:31:56.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"}},"lgg":{"14d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":143436.13,"percent":96.17}],"7d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":143436.13,"percent":96.17}],"4d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":143436.13,"percent":96.17}],"36h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":143436.13,"percent":96.17}],"24h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":143436.13,"percent":96.17}],"12h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":143436.13,"percent":96.17}]},"lastGroomedGroups":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":5566.72,"percent":3.73}],"active":true,"timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[37.662366946023944,-118.98669369563093],"distance":149141.9834562198,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":149.14,"percent":100}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.mammothtrails.org/"}},"elevation":2516,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2026-02-12T18:36:37.574Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-7","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-07T00:13:13.879Z","clubId":"US-CA-Mammoth","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>We were able to get out and groom the A-B-K loop yesterday, and the conditions are still holding out &nbsp;ok on those trails that are at higher elevation and west of 395. Due to full melt out on the A trail leaving shady rest, we will not be grooming any more this season. Thanks and looking forward to the next one!\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The USFS has ploughed Deadman Creek rd, so please use caution in that area, especially if traveling off trail.\u003C/p>"},"account":"675ca6440d1165b1750308c2","author":"Andrew","timestamp":"2026-03-07T00:05:49.000Z","deviceId":"4E1C64AA-E23D-4A6A-BE98-D53353A12B5D"},"reportNotices":[{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.886Z","clubId":"US-CA-Mammoth","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>The USDA Forest Service will begin an emergency operation to trap and move up to 25 snow-bound wild horses located on the Inyo National Forest outside the Montgomery Pass Wild Horse Territory. This emergency action is critical to ensuring the future health, well-being, and humane treatment of these wild horses as they are in critical jeopardy due to snow impact, limited water, and extremely limited forage.\u003Cbr>\u003Cbr>Effective from January 17 at 9 a.m. through January 27, going into or being within the Bald Mountain Closure Area is prohibited within the Inyo National Forest. Due to the nature of the bait and water trap method, wild horses are reluctant to approach the trap site when there is too much activity; therefore, only essential personnel will be allowed at the trap site during the operation. We ask the public to not interfere with the operation.\u003Cbr>\u003Cbr>Multiple Over-Snow Vehicle (OSV) routes are affected by this closure, including portions of Trail I, Trail D, I and D Connector Trail. Travel on the trails within the closure is prohibited. The closure area is shown on the map. Contact: SM.FS.InyoWH_B@usda.gov\u003C/p>"},"account":"67608920ffdc829309aa2024","author":"Gretchen","timestamp":"2026-01-18T03:10:16.950Z","images":["2026-01-17T19-10-24-081-08:00_US-CA-Mammoth_0.jpg"]}]},{"clubId":"US-NH-Nansen","season":"winter","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"NH","permalink":"Nansen-Ski-Club","bounds":[[-71.23201663019879,44.56712727268415],[-71.2191812363146,44.57788331340913]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca5ce"],"name":{"en":"Nansen Ski Club Trails"},"city":{"en":"Berlin"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>The Nansen Ski Club is the oldest continually operating ski club in America, established in the late 1800's. We provide groomed Nordic ski &amp; snowshoe trails at Milan Hill State Park in northern New Hampshire, while we also work to restore \"The Big Nansen\" - a 172 foot ski jump which hosted the first Olympic jumping trials in 1938.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Our mission is to bring outdoor winter recreation and fun to the people of the North Country and beyond. We are 100% volunteer operated, with our work made possible through memberships, donations and sponsorships from our generous local business community. Non-members are welcome to try our trails with a single-day pass that can be paid for at the trailhead.&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Check out our website for historical information and learn more about our club!\u003C/p>"},"region":"New Hampshire","country":"USA","logo":"2024-07-10T13-53-55-583-06:00_US-NH-Nansen_logo.png","banner":"2025-12-11T10-19-30-106-05:00_US-NH-Nansen_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"24h":{"ts":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"12h":{"ts":"2026-03-06T03:03:54.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"}},"lgg":{"14d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":8604.21,"percent":98.23}],"7d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":8604.21,"percent":98.23}],"4d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":8604.21,"percent":98.23}],"36h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":8604.21,"percent":98.23}],"24h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":8604.21,"percent":98.23}],"12h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":8604.21,"percent":98.23}]},"active":true,"timezone":"America/New_York","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[44.57766778432149,-71.22524816489225],"distance":8758.868924920462,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":2.14,"percent":24.409190342236815},{"id":"intermediate","distance":4.68,"percent":53.473301230231144},{"id":"advanced","distance":1.94,"percent":22.11750842753203}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.skinansen.com/"},"weather":{"en":"https://www.yr.no/en/forecast/daily-table/44.578,-71.226"}},"elevation":459,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2025-12-11T15:15:33.512Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-4","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-27T12:46:56.307Z","clubId":"US-NH-Nansen","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>It looks like northeastern spring is doing its thing with the mild temps yesterday and now a freeze for the weekend. I will admit, I (Amy) am writing this without seeing the trails, but my guess is that the warm ungroomed soft snow of yesterday is going to harden right up with this wind and nights in the teens making for a hard packed, icy trail surface. Skiing is not recommended for safety reasons. Snowshoeing is still a possibility.&nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"675263a33e664affbf34afdc","author":"Nansen Admin","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:46:46.464Z"}},{"clubId":"US-VT-NorthStRidge","activities":["nordic","snowshoe"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"VT","permalink":"North-St-Ridge","bounds":[[-72.56798614385926,44.2799250668135],[-72.53879925573392,44.311176943569905]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca622"],"name":{"en":"Onion River Nordic Trails"},"city":{"en":"Montpelier"},"groomedBy":{"en":"Montpelier Parks Department"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>This area is maintained for skiing in partnership with Montpelier Parks, Onion River Nordic Ski Club, and many generous landowners. This area is ALL on private land, so please be courteous and respect the rules below in order to honor the generosity of the landowners who allow public use on their property.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Where to Park:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Along North St. (please do not park with 50 yards of the intersection with Sparrow Farm Rd.)\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>At the plowed field lots on Cummings Rd. (at corner of North st.) and County Rd (across from the gray barn at Morse Farm.)\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Guidelines for Use:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>No walkers or fat bikes. Snowshoes are welcome.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>No dogs (note that landowners may have dogs on their own property).\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Stay on the groomed trails, as those are the areas where public access is granted. Please do not follow ski tracks off the groomed path.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Please use only during daylight hours.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Vermont","country":"USA","regions":["US-VT-Central-Vermont"],"logo":"2024-12-12T20-07-33-108-07:00_US-VT-NorthStRidge_logo_0.png","banner":"2024-12-12T20-15-30-921-07:00_US-VT-NorthStRidge_Rob_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"24h":{"ts":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"12h":{"ts":"2026-03-04T16:39:31.639Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"}},"lgg":{"14d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14935.27,"percent":97.22}],"7d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14935.27,"percent":97.22}],"4d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14935.27,"percent":97.22}],"36h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14935.27,"percent":97.22}],"24h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14935.27,"percent":97.22}],"12h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14935.27,"percent":97.22}]},"lastGroomedGroups":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":14622.74,"percent":95.19}],"active":true,"timezone":"America/New_York","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[44.28429266054492,-72.54661222269338],"distance":15361.701832902972,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":12.22,"percent":79.51963247168422},{"id":"intermediate","distance":3.15,"percent":20.48036752831577}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.montpelier-vt.org/292/Maps-and-Trail-Conditions#:~:text=Certain%20trails%20at%20Hubbard%20Park,to%20put%20on%20ice%20spikes."}},"elevation":355,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2025-02-04T21:42:09.251Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-4","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-13T12:39:02.461Z","clubId":"US-VT-NorthStRidge","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Well it appears we may be done for the season folks. Before you fall into complete despair, let's gather for a celebration of our amazing local Nordic Ski Trail Network and all the volunteers and landowners who make it possible. See the attached poster or the info below for details:\u003Cbr>WHAT: Celebration Dinner\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>WHERE: Montpelier High School Cafeteria\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>WHEN: Sat. March 28\u003Cbr>4:30pm Ski sprints and snow games for all ages (dependent on snow conditions)\u003Cbr>5:30pm Lasagna Dinner (with garlic bread, salads, desserts, GF options)!WHO: Local ski community (any of you who enjoy skiing off County Road or Cummings Street, at the old Elk's Club, or in Hubbard Park. )\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>WHY: To give thanks to all the volunteers and land owners who make this community resource available.\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>HOW: Please register and pay in advance with this link:\u003Cbr>https://www.paypal.com/ncp/payment/N3CDFKABRE2SE\u003Cbr>This will let us plan food accordingly.\u003Cbr>$20 Adult, $40 Family, $10 Student.\u003Cbr>Limited day-of registration for an extra $5.\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>There will also be a fundraising raffle for continued support of local skiing. Prizes from Onion River Outdoors, Catamount Trail Association, Hunger Mountain Coop, Craftsbury Outdoor Center, Jasper Hill Cheese and More!\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>Call Nancy Chickering (802) 223-0577 with questions or to volunteer to help with serving, clean-up, or bringing gluten-free food options.\u003C/p>"},"account":"6712a0fdc3b2da0e067d76b5","author":"Alec","timestamp":"2026-03-13T12:38:51.487Z","images":["2026-03-13T08-38-58-289-04:00_US-VT-NorthStRidge_0.jpg"]}},{"clubId":"US-VT-Montpelier","activities":["nordic","snowshoe","fatbike"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"VT","permalink":"City-Of-Montpelier-Trails","bounds":[[-72.58222574751441,44.26137767275795],[-72.56049460721246,44.2915648134783]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-04T13:57:46.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca616"],"name":{"en":"City of Montpelier Parks Trails"},"city":{"en":"Montpelier"},"groomedBy":{"en":"Parks Department"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>Montpelier's Parks are groomed for Winter use by Parks staff and volunteers. These trails are shared by skiers, walkers, and in some places fat bikers.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Where to Park:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Anywhere inside Hubbard Park\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>At the Pool on Elm St. to access the North Branch Park\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>At the North Branch Nature Center\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Guidelines for Use:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Walkers are welcome on these trails. Please use snow-shoes if your feet are sinking more than 1\" into soft snow as that really helps us keep the trails in good shape for everyone.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Dogs are welcome on these trails and may be off-leash in the northern area of Hubbard Park if owners follow the Hubbard Park Canine Code of Conduct. See signs on-site for more details.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Fat Bikes are welcome on all the trails in the North Branch Park and on the main wide trails in Hubbard Park.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Vermont","country":"USA","regions":["US-VT-Central-Vermont"],"groups":[{"groupId":"Mont