is ample parking on-site at Country Club Rd.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Guidelines for Use:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Please no walkers on the wide ski trails. There is a 6' wide perimeter loop groomed for walking, so walkers can continue to enjoy this area in the winter.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Dogs may be here if on leash or under voice control per City rules.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Fat bikes are allowed.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Vermont","country":"USA","regions":["US-VT-Central-Vermont"],"logo":"2024-12-04T09-56-30-676-05:00_US-VT-Montpelier_logo_0.png","banner":"2024-10-18T12-46-19-397-06:00_US-VT-Montpelier_Rob.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-02-20T02:41:20.202Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-02-20T02:41:20.202Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-02-20T02:41:20.202Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026-02-20T02:41:20.202Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"24h":{"ts":"2026-02-20T02:41:20.202Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"12h":{"ts":"2026-02-20T02:41:20.202Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"}},"lgg":{"14d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}],"7d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}],"4d":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}],"36h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}],"24h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}],"12h":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}]},"lastGroomedGroups":[{"id":"twoWeeksAgo","distance":4261.51,"percent":100}],"active":true,"timezone":"America/New_York","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[44.246441827094024,-72.54491280753281],"distance":4261.514690606935,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":4.26,"percent":100}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://onionrivernordic.org/places-to-ski/"}},"snowDepth":1,"elevation":195,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2024-11-08T22:54:48.828Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-4","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-13T12:42:38.534Z","clubId":"US-VT-ElksClub","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Well it appears we may be done for the season folks. Before you fall into complete despair, let's gather for a celebration of our amazing local Nordic Ski Trail Network and all the volunteers and landowners who make it possible. See the attached poster or the info below for details:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cbr>WHAT: Celebration Dinner\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>WHERE: Montpelier High School Cafeteria\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>WHEN: Sat. March 28\u003Cbr>4:30pm Ski sprints and snow games for all ages (dependent on snow conditions)\u003Cbr>5:30pm Lasagna Dinner (with garlic bread, salads, desserts, GF options)!WHO: Local ski community (any of you who enjoy skiing off County Road or Cummings Street, at the old Elk's Club, or in Hubbard Park. )\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>WHY: To give thanks to all the volunteers and land owners who make this community resource available.\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>HOW: Please register and pay in advance with this link:\u003Cbr>https://www.paypal.com/ncp/payment/N3CDFKABRE2SE\u003Cbr>This will let us plan food accordingly.\u003Cbr>$20 Adult, $40 Family, $10 Student.\u003Cbr>Limited day-of registration for an extra $5.\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>There will also be a fundraising raffle for continued support of local skiing. Prizes from Onion River Outdoors, Catamount Trail Association, Hunger Mountain Coop, Craftsbury Outdoor Center, Jasper Hill Cheese and More!\u003Cbr>&nbsp;\u003Cbr>Call Nancy Chickering (802) 223-0577 with questions or to volunteer to help with serving, clean-up, or bringing gluten-free food options.\u003C/p>"},"account":"6712a0fdc3b2da0e067d76b5","author":"Alec","timestamp":"2026-03-13T12:42:13.865Z","images":["2026-03-13T08-42-23-539-04:00_US-VT-ElksClub_0.jpg","2026-03-13T08-42-23-539-04:00_US-VT-ElksClub_1.jpg"],"imagesMeta":[{"createdAt":"2026-03-13T12:42:40.831Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-13T12:42:40.831Z","name":"2026-03-13T08-42-23-539-04:00_US-VT-ElksClub_0.jpg","description":"Cross Country Skiing at Country Club Rd","alt":"Country Club Rd",