ery Saturday and Sunday.&nbsp; The Apple Kitchen\u003C/span>\u003Cspan> also serves a variety of New York State craft brews and their own signature wine, Orchard Ridge.\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cspan>Consider supporting these welcoming hosts by visiting their business before or after a peaceful hike, snowshoe, or ski!!\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cspan>https://www.johnnyshoppes.com/\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>Trails are groomed in winter for xc-skiing and snowshoeing, courtesy of FROSTY:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Friends of Stoney Pond exists to foster year-round outdoor recreation through its efforts in trail development and maintenance, snow grooming, snowshoe rentals, and advocacy of human-powered trails-based activities throughout Madison County.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Equipment and volunteers are made available to local organizations&ndash;&ndash;to assist in the expansion and usability of trail networks on public and private lands.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>FROSTY participates in the NYS DEC Volunteer Stewardship program, which enhances use of NYS public lands. As a registered 501(c)(3) 100% funded by donors, donations are invested in tools, equipment and supplies utilized exclusively on local trail networks.\u003C/p>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>US-20 east; turn right on Erieville Road; turn left on Old State Road\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>US-20 west; turn left on Willowvale Road; turn right on Old State Road\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>From the south: turn on Old State Road from Erieville Road\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>https://goo.gl/maps/dSZqzuStoZcQ9Y3MA\u003C/p>\n"},"region":"New York","country":"USA","logo":"2023-07-14T10-17-16-093-07:00_US-NY-StoneyPond_logo.png","banner":"2023-07-21T10-55-31-612-04:00_US-NY-Appleseed_Rob.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2026-02-01T15:49:35.933Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2026-02-01T15:49:35.933Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2026-02-01T15:49:35.933Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2026