n":"\u003Cdiv id=\"block-yui_3_17_2_1_1680288889024_7751\" data-block-type=\"2\" data-border-radii=\"{&quot;topLeft&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0},&quot;topRight&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0},&quot;bottomLeft&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0},&quot;bottomRight&quot;:{&quot;unit&quot;:&quot;px&quot;,&quot;value&quot;:0.0}}\" data-sqsp-block=\"text\">\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cdiv data-sqsp-text-block-content=\"\">\n\u003Ch3>Beartooth Trails promotes non-motorized winter recreation and transportation activities by leasing and operating the Red Lodge Nordic Center, located 2 miles west of Red Lodge off Highway 78. We&rsquo;ve laid out over 15K of groomed trails to take advantage of the inspiring views and easy-going nature of the terrain. With a warming hut and restroom, this is a great place for families to get out and have some affordable fun!\u003C/h3>\n\u003Ch3>\u003Ca href=\"https://beartoothtrails.org/grooming-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Grooming\u003C/a> typically takes place on Saturday, Sunday &amp; Monday. Weather and conditions can change the grooming schedule so please refer to the Grooming Report for Nordic Center status.\u003C/h3>\n\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1763929783307_517\">\n\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1763929783307_516\">\n\u003Cdiv id=\"block-yui_3_17_2_1_1680288889024_2951\" data-block-json=\"{&quot;hSize&quot;:null,&quot;floatDir&quot;:null,&quot;methodOption&quot;:&quot;existing&quot;,&quot;existingGallery&quot;:&quot;5e323886b4e70977cffa4618&quot;,&quot;newWindow&quot;:false,&quot;active-alignment&quot;:&quot;center&quot;,&quot;aspectRatio&quot;:null,&quot;auto-crop&quot;:true,&quot;autoplay&quot;:false,&quot;blockAnimation&quot;:&quot;none&quot;,&quot;collectionId&quot;:&quot;5e323886b4e70977cffa4618&quot;,&quot;controls&quot;:false,&quot;design&quot;:&quot;slideshow&quot;,&quot;existingGalleryId&quot;:&quot;5e323886b4e70977cffa4618&quot;,&quot;meta-position&quot;:&quot;bottom&quot;,&quot;show-meta&quot;:true,&quot;show-meta-basic&quot;:true,&quot;show-meta-only-title&quot;:false,&quot;show-meta-only-description&quot;:false,&quot;show-meta-on-hover&quot;:false,&quot;square-thumbs&quot;:true,&quot;thumbnail-strip-height&quot;:80,&quot;thumbnail-strip-margin&quot;:20,&quot;thumbnails&quot;:false,&quot;vSize&quot;:null}\" data-block-type=\"8\">\n\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1763929783307_515\">\n\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1763929783307_199\">\n\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1763929783307_216\">\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Ch3>\u003Ca title=\"Directions-Red Lodge Nordic Center\" href=\"https://maps.app.goo.gl/qibnB38VuHRvsEhh8\">Google Maps-Red Lodge Nordic Center\u003C/a>\u003C/h3>\n\u003Ch3>Take Highway 78 one mile west from the Red Lodge* roundabout; turn left onto Fox Road (after the cemetery). Follow Fox Road west about one mile to the next intersection (Fox &amp; Smith Roads), and turn right at the RLNC sign (and Aspen Ridge Ranch sign) on Smith Rd. The parking lot is about 1/2 mile north on Smith road. No parking on the road.\u003C/h3>\n\u003Ch3>lat. 45.20156, long -109.28195\u003C/h3>"},"region":"Montana","country":"USA","groups":[{"groupId":"NordicTrails","groupName":"Nordic Trails","groupBounds":[[-109.30735254797898,45.19559837198125],[-109.2790866569701,45.204647953357934]]},{"groupId":"SnowshoeTrails","groupOrder":1,"groupName":"Snow Shoe Trails","groupBounds":[[-109.29711416484447,45.19549802501952],[-109.27885436549963,45.20459924769792]]}],"banner":"2026-02-04T16-08-24-632-07:00_US-MT-RedLodgeNordicCenter_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","lgc":{"14d":{"ts":"2025-12-28T17:05:18.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"7d":{"ts":"2025-12-28T17:05:18.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"4d":{"ts":"2025-12-28T17:05:18.000Z","cl":"twoWeeksAgo"},"36h":{"ts":"2025-12-28T17:05:18.000Z","cl":"twoW