-09T23:47:01.026Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-20T22:26:39.549Z","clubId":"AB-WestBragg","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Hi folks! After a glorious three days of brilliant skiing last weekend, the latest chinook blew in decimating the snow on our trails, and bringing down a lot of forest debris. I hope that many of you were able to do some sliding when it was good as it seems unlikely that conditions will improve between now and the end of March when grooming season officially ends. Hope you can find some decent snow further west at higher elevations. If we are in fact done for the season all our groomers look forward to seeing you next winter.&nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"692f34d3dd42915ab023bdc6","author":"ptFalcon","timestamp":"2026-03-20T22:19:34.000Z","deviceId":"D6434E62-A9FA-4953-A37A-B9CFDCA421A8"}},{"clubId":"AB-Goldbar","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"CA","regionId":"AB","permalink":"Edmonton-Goldbar","bounds":[[-113.4302324,53.5417561],[-113.4014722,53.5606748]],"lastGroomed":"2026-04-01T02:59:43.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e5e3004a71b66ca17a"],"name":{"en":"Gold Bar / Gold Stick & Capilano"},"city":{"en":"Edmonton"},"region":"Alberta","country":"Canada","regions":["EdmontonArea","EdmontonCity"],"logo":"2024-01-15T18-05-33-375-05:00_AB-Goldbar_logo.png","banner":"AB-Goldbar-banner.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","active":true,"timezone":"America/Edmonton","liveTrack":true,"trackset":true,"tracksetType":"tracksetManual","coordinates":[53.557637,-113.407565],"distance":"12778.11853629362","distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":3.99,"percent":31.18938037113682},{"id":"intermediate","distance":2.93,"percent":22.90483431625944},{"id":"advanced","distance":5.87,"percent":45.90578531260374}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.edmontonnordic.ca/"},"weather":{"en":"https://weather.gc.ca/city/pages/ab-50_metric_e.html"}},"sponsorLogo":"2024-01-15T18-05-33-375-05:00_AB-Goldbar_logo.png","elevation":622,"tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-04-08T04:14:36.790Z","clubId":"AB-Goldbar","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>We tried our best to do something with today's snow, unfortunately it was very wet and the moisture in the base was not easy to work with. \u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The conditions are considered bad to terrible and are barely skiable. There is still snow on the trails, but skiing is not recommended.&nbsp;\u003Cbr />\u003Cbr />\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>We will see if conditions change in the next day or so, but this might be our last attempt at grooming.&nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"6760ad20ffdc829309aaee33","author":"Dean","timestamp":"2026-04-08T04:11:11.000Z","deviceId":"4B5EC3B3-C54C-455D-9D21-6C13E45D92CD"},"reportNotices":[{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.184Z","clubId":"AB-Goldbar","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1770231108646_382\" data-slice-type=\"heading\" data-slice-id=\"6952d2a328cc2d6dd37606ea\">\n\u003Ch1 id=\"sqs-slash-page-header\">ALBERTA CUP EVENT FEBRUARY 7&amp;8\u003C/h1>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1770231108646_404\" data-slice-type=\"body\" data-slice-id=\"6952d2a328cc2d6dd37606eb\">\n\u003Cp id=\"yui_3_17_2_1_1770231108646_445\" data-rte-preserve-empty=\"true\">On February 7th &amp; 8th there will be races taking place at Gold Bar park from 7am to 4pm. Please avoid using trails during this time. Capilano and Gold Stick will be open for skiing.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>"},"account":"6760ad20ffdc829309aaee33","author":"Dean","timestamp":"2026-02-04T18:50:59.000Z","deviceId":"4B5EC3B3-C54C-455D-9D21-6C13E45D92CD"}]},{"clubId":"AB-StrathconaWilderness","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"CA","regionId":"AB","permalink":"Strathcona-Wilderness","bounds":[[-113.0126667,53.5287905],[-112.9762216,53.5410636]],"lastGroomed":"2026-04-07T15:49:32.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e5e3004a71b66ca182"],"name":{"en":"Strathcona Wilderness Centre"},"city":{"en":"Strathcona County"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>Coming from Highway 16 - turn south on RR 212 and drive straight until you reach the main gates\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Coming from Baseline Road (TWP 530) - turn south on RR 212\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Coming from Wye Road (HWY 630) - turn north on RR 213, then right on TWP 530, right on RR 212\u003C/p>"},"region":"Alberta","country":"Canada","regions":["EdmontonArea","US-CCSAA"],"logo":"AB-StrathconaWilderness.png","banner":"AB-StrathconaWilderness-banner.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","active":true,"timezone":"America/Edmonton","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[53.5327696,-112.9996214],"distance":"16645.159259641503","distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":8.7,"percent":52.26364137536795},{"id":"intermediate","distance":5.64,"percent":33.90667362226502},{"id":"advanced","distance":2.3,"percent":13.82968500236702}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.strathcona.ca/recreation-events/recreation-centres/strathcona-wilderness-centre/"}},"currentCond":"Excellent","waxKick":"Green","elevation":757,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2023-04-11T01:41:57.355Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-04-07T21:34:47.427Z","clubId":"AB-StrathconaWilderness","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cem>\u003Cspan data-olk-copy-source=\"MessageBody\">Due to unexpected equipment issues, trail grooming at SWC is temporarily unavailable. Skiers may still access the trails but do so at their own risk. No on‑site safety or rescue services are available, and emergency response times may be delayed.\u003C/span>\u003C/em>\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cem>As a result, trail use is free at this time. Visitors should be prepared for self‑sufficient travel, use caution, and ski within their abilities while considering current trail and weather conditions.\u003C/em>\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>"},"account":"65ca8c8797363ffec4d1aefa","author":"Paulina","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:31:54.804Z"},"reportNotices":[{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.190Z","clubId":"AB-StrathconaWilderness","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Due to equipment challenges grooming is still in process. &nbsp;\u003Cbr />\u003Cbr />Trails are in fair condition due to icey sections and debris from winds. &nbsp;\u003Cbr />\u003Cbr />\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Multi purpose was completed but the focus will be on wagon and owl on the east side, then back to the west side for moose and deer. &nbsp;\u003Cbr />\u003Cbr />\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Be aware of debris on both classic and skate lanes. &nbsp;Classic tracks are icey. &nbsp;\u003Cbr />\u003Cbr />\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Further update later this morning. &nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"695169623f2411a7b25a87be","author":"SWC Groomer","timestamp":"2026-01-16T15:45:14.000Z","deviceId":"960C5DFC-07F2-459F-B8AD-2BFC3ED11304"},{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.190Z","clubId":"AB-StrathconaWilderness","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Land Trails\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>East Trails have been reset and are in good condition&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>West trails was last reset march 3rd and fresh corduroy this morning and are in good condition&nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Classic : Good condition\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Skate: Good condition&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Bennett Lake\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Bennett lake is currently being reset for both classic and skate tracks.\u003C/p>"},"account":"695169623f2411a7b25a87be","author":"SWC Groomer","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:13:53.000Z","deviceId":"960C5DFC-07F2-459F-B8AD-2BFC3ED11304"},{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.190Z","clubId":"AB-StrathconaWilderness","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Due to a delay west side trails are being finished and should be done by 9:30 am &nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>East side trail skate lanes were groomed this morning and classic track was set March 26&n