5837]]]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-28T23:17:22.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca37a"],"name":{"en":"Bear Valley Adventure Company"},"city":{"en":"Bear Valley"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>Our cross country skiing guests enjoy an extensive trail system with 60+ kilometers of groomed trails across 3,000 acres. We have 38 carefully groomed trails for track and skate skiing, a trailside&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https://www.bvadventures.com/meadow-cafe\">Meadow Cafe\u003C/a>, and three warming huts throughout the trail system. No pets are allowed on our trail system. The 7,000- to 7,800-foot elevation enables early opening (usually Thanksgiving Weekend) and late-season closure (usually mid-April). If you haven't experienced Bear Valley Nordic skiing, it's worth being on your bucket list. Cheers!\u003C/p>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>We are located 2 hours drive east of Stockton, California, on State Highway 4.&nbsp; From Arnold, California, you are 30 minutes away clear roads. When arriving in Bear Valley, you will see the large meadow on your right (south), and the village entrance on your left.&nbsp; We are the first building when you enter the village. We are also the local gas station. We have limited parking at our store, but plenty of additional parking in the village within walking distance from the store.\u003C/p>"},"region":"California","country":"USA","regions":["US-CCSAA"],"banner":"2022-11-11T11-59-07-100-08:00_US-CA-BearValley_Julien.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"oneDayAgo","active":true,"timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[38.455595,-120.040791],"distance":42480.04450032204,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":12.57,"percent":29.5811386067156},{"id":"intermediate","distance":18.68,"percent":43.966466189354065},{"id":"advanced","distance":11.24,"percent":26.452395203930397}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.bvadventures.com/"},"weather":{"en":"https://weather.com/weather/tenday/l/383219f43c7deb9be0a07a1f7383