ppointment, please call 715-356-1099.\u003C/p>"},"account":"68f049e40661e9b99f8bb6df","author":"Jason","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:48:59.000Z","deviceId":"9EA4C5D8-C4D4-4A65-AA1A-5BCB03648FB9"}},{"clubId":"US-NH-DublinSchool","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"NH","permalink":"Dublin-School-Nordic-Center","bounds":[[-72.07737337215198,42.90516927307641],[-72.04871336419592,42.92341971379982]],"lastGroomed":"2025-03-23T13:02:39.404Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca48e"],"name":{"en":"Dublin School Nordic Center"},"city":{"en":"Dublin"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>The Dublin School Nordic Center opened in January 2014. The 9 km trail system, &nbsp;provides the school with a state of the art training and racing facility to complement its long-existing 20 km trail system below Dublin Road. By combining the School's trails with those of Yankee Publishing's trails, skiers can now ski from the Dublin General Store to the summit of Beech Hill. The trails are designed to be challenging and fun, with lots of twists and turns to keep young people entertained while developing important skills and balance for the sport.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>In 2015 the International Ski Federation (FIS) voted to award Dublin School&rsquo;s Nordic Center a homologation certificate for it&rsquo;s five kilometer John Morton designed race course. The homologation process establishes an international standard for race courses to provide guidelines for course design and construction. Today the School is adding an extensive snowmaking and lighting system to one of its race loops. The course plans to or has hosted College Carnivals, Eastern Cups, Prep School races, and BKL and Citizen&rsquo;s races.\u003C/p>"},"region":"New Hampshire","country":"USA","logo":"2023-06-07T10-47-46-337-06:00_US-NH-DublinSchool_logo.png","banner":"2023-06-16T09-56-10-612-06:00_US-NH-DublinSchool_Rob.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"fourDaysAgo","active":true,"timezone":"America/New_York","liveTrack":true,"coo