032458468,45.833121918741654],[-110.87957032458468,45.83323831164975],[-110.88028744326691,45.83323831164975],[-110.88028744326691,45.83476472016221],[-110.88082750069835,45.83476472016221],[-110.88082750069835,45.83577205703751],[-110.88327003665074,45.83577205703751],[-110.88327003665074,45.837751633347345],[-110.88569343026255,45.837751633347345],[-110.88569343026255,45.84255740152952],[-110.88576247359417,45.84255740152952],[-110.88576247359417,45.845145532991424],[-110.88588350090124,45.845145532991424],[-110.88588350090124,45.845396020094725],[-110.89088478653886,45.845396020094725],[-110.89088478653886,45.84896662007208],[-110.9070176326883,45.84896662007208],[-110.9070176326883,45.84875274735692],[-110.90876444206332,45.84875274735692],[-110.90876444206332,45.848033020078006],[-110.91366958213057,45.848033020078006],[-110.91366958213057,45.84583327585276],[-110.91681225616642,45.84583327585276],[-110.91681225616642,45.83519811650374]]]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-08T12:20:40.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca5aa"],"name":{"en":"Crosscut Mountain Sports Center"},"nameS":{"en":"Crosscut"},"city":{"en":"Bozeman"},"sponsorText":{"en":"\u003Cp>Crosscut Mountain Sports Center Grooming Report Sponsored by Treeline Coffee Roasters.\u003C/p>"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>Crosscut Mountain Sports Center is a year-round mountain hub providing human-powered recreation, sports training, and outdoor education for all ages, abilities, identities, and backgrounds.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Located just 17 miles north of Bozeman in the heart of the Bridger Range, Crosscut sits on 500 acres adjacent to Bridger Bowl and the Custer Gallatin National Forest. From Nordic skiing and snowshoeing to biking and hiking, we love helping folks enjoy the outdoors in every season.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>As a nonprofit, Crosscut is dedicated to serving the community and stewarding our shared lands. With welcoming facilities and extraordinary trails amidst pristine natural beauty, we offer connection, solitude, and inspiration for our community and those who wish to visit.\u003C/p>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Ca title=\"Crosscut Base Area\" href=\"https://maps.app.goo.gl/2NKhQ6kPMn3Z9YaS7\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://maps.app.goo.gl/2NKhQ6kPMn3Z9YaS7\u003C/a>\u003C/p>"},"region":"Montana","country":"USA","groups":[{"groupId":"Crosscut","groupName":"Ski Trails","groupBounds":[[-110.91164872992644,45.81823094689437],[-110.88306567071655,45.84536951309448]]},{"groupId":"CCNarrowGauge","groupOrder":1,"groupName":"Narrow Gauge Trails","groupBounds":[[-110.89999695882669,45.82018490330291],[-110.88306575938529,45.84154842599055]]}],"logo":"2025-01-06T16-03-30-784-07:00_US-MT-Crosscut_logo_0.png","banner":"2025-11-29T17-47-57-084-08:00_US-MT-Crosscut_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","active":true,"timezone":"America/Edmonton","liveTrack":true,"trackset":true,"tracksetType":"tracksetChecked","coordinates":[45.82844084504928,-110.88324456219856],"distance":42021.87454841876,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":12.83,"percent":30.520156571451622},{"id":"intermediate","distance":20.69,"percent":49.23974037063516},{"id":"advanced","distance":8.51,"percent":20.24010305791326}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.crosscutmt.org/"},"weather":{"en":"https://www.crosscutmt.org/grooming-and-conditions#current-weather"}},"sponsor":true,"sponsorLogo":"2024-11-24T22-15-31-443-08:00_US-MT-Crosscut_logo_0.png","sponsorLink":"https://treelinecoffee.com/","currentCond":"firm and fast","elevation":1850,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2025-12-27T18:07:18.878Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-04-03T12:40:11.151Z","clubId":"US-MT-Crosscut","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>**Friday 7am update: We are going to try and get a skiff of grooming for you today! It won't last long, and the cautionary advice below still applies, but we have some good snow for now! We better show Mother Nature that we appreciate it, even if a bit late.**\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>As of midday today, the entire Crosscut trail system was bare &mdash; no snow coverage anywhere on the trail network. We've had rain and sleet throughout the day, with heavy wet snow moving in this evening. Season pass holders may ski if they wish, but please keep the following in mind before heading out:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>&bull; No support services are available\u003C/strong>, including incident response and emergency evacuation. Skiing is entirely at each pass holder's own risk.\u003Cbr />\u003Cstrong>&bull; Conditions are unpredictable.\u003C/strong> Heavy, wet snow on bare ground is tricky. Expect uneven coverage, debris, and variable surfaces. Ski conservatively and stay in control at all times.\u003Cbr />\u003Cstrong>&bull; Rock skis strongly recommended.\u003C/strong> Snow is falling on bare ground, and rocks, roots, sticks, and other hazards lurk just beneath the surface. Treat this like a first snowfall in October situation.\u003Cbr />\u003Cstrong>&bull;&nbsp;\u003C/strong>With temperatures forecast to reach 40&deg;F on Friday and 50&deg;F on Saturday, any snow accumulation will likely be short-lived. \u003Cstrong>We do not plan to groom.\u003C/strong>\u003Cbr />\u003Cstrong>&bull; \u003C/strong>Please be aware that there may be people walking on the trails.\u003Cbr />\u003Cstrong>&bull; \u003C/strong>Dogs are allowed.\u003Cbr />\u003Cstrong>&bull; \u003C/strong>For current conditions and a livestream view of the Base Area, visit \u003Cstrong>\u003Cem>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.crosscutmt.org/grooming-and-conditions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">C\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"https://www.crosscutmt.org/grooming-and-conditions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">rosscut's Grooming &amp; Conditions webpage\u003C/a>\u003C/em>\u003Cem>.\u003C/em>\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>"},"account":"65fc61737aba11e90246d39a","author":"Laurie","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:54:26.000Z"}},{"clubId":"FR-SA-LesSaisies","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"FR","regionId":"FR-SA","permalink":"Domaine-Nordique-Les-Saisies","bounds":[[6.5074276,45.7522214],[6.5321767,45.7834305]],"lastGroomed":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca5b2"],"name":{"en":"Domaine Nordique des Saisies","fr":"Domaine Nordique des Saisies"},"nameS":{"en":"Les Saisies","fr":"Les Saisies"},"city":{"en":"Hauteluce","fr":"Hauteluce"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>The Les Saisies Nordic ski area is renowned for being one of the largest Nordic ski areas&nbsp;in France.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>In 1992, the resort hosted the cross-country skiing and biathlon events at the Albertville Winter Olympics, contributing to its reputation as a leading Nordic ski destination. The 120 km ski area has been awarded the Site d&rsquo;excellence 4 sapins label by Nordic France.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Thanks to its high altitude, the Les Saisies Nordic ski area is one of the best snow-covered in the Alps.&nbsp;Skiing takes place here every year from mid-November (thanks to snowfarming) to the end of April.\u003C/p>","fr":"\u003Cp>Le domaine de ski nordique des Saisies est r&eacute;put&eacute; pour &ecirc;tre l&rsquo;un des plus grands domaines de ski nordique en France.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>En 1992, la station a accueilli les &eacute;preuves de ski de fond et de biathlon lors des Jeux Olympiques d&rsquo;hiver d&rsquo;Albertville, ce qui a contribu&eacute; &agrave; sa renomm&eacute;e comme destination de ski nordique de premier plan. Le Domaine de 120 km est labellis&eacute; Site d&rsquo;excellence 4 sapins par Nordic France.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Gr&acirc;ce &agrave; son altitude &eacute;lev&eacute;e, le domaine nordique des Saisies est l&rsquo;un des mieux enneig&eacute;s des Alpes. On y skie chaque ann&eacute;e d&egrave;s le 18 novembre (gr&acirc;ce au snowfarming)&nbsp; jusqu&rsquo;&agrave; fin avril.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Savoie","country":"France","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","active":true,"timezone":"Europe/Paris",