57255207,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":3.05,"percent":100}],"snowDepth":5,"currentTemp":-11,"currentCond":"Poor","elevation":719,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2025-12-11T18:39:53.804Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-16T19:53:57.004Z","clubId":"AB-Broadmoor","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Ski Trail Update\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Thank you to everyone who came out and made use of the ski trails this season. We truly appreciate the support from the community throughout the winter.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>This year brought a number of ups and downs with trail and weather conditions, but overall it was a positive season and we were happy to provide the trails for everyone to enjoy.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The ski trails are now \u003Cstrong>officially closed for the season\u003C/strong> as we begin shifting our focus toward preparations for the upcoming golf season.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Please note that the trails will \u003Cstrong>no longer be groomed or monitored\u003C/strong>. Anyone choosing to continue using the trails does so \u003Cstrong>at their own risk\u003C/strong>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Thank you again for joining us this winter, and we look forward to welcoming everyone back as we transition into the golf season.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>&mdash; BPGC Team\u003C/p>"},"account":"6931ab2d85ef257d5a59351d","author":"Groomer MC","timestamp":"2026-03-16T19:53:38.761Z","snowDepth":5,"currentTemp":-11,"currentCond":"Poor"}},{"clubId":"US-WA-LWSCGolf","activities":["nordic","snowshoe"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"WA","permalink":"Leavenworth-Golf-Course","bounds":[[-120.67449205017289,47.57430067191377],[-120.66577062209421,47.58717031263789]],"weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca66e"],"name":{"en":"Leavenworth Golf Course"},"city":{"en":"Leavenworth"},"groomedBy":{"en":"Leavenworth Winter Sports Club"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>The Leavenworth Winter Sports Club maintains 26km of tracks and skating lanes that offer a variety of skiing terrain across three areas around Leavenworth. Each location offers a slightly different experience both in scenery and terrain.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https://skileavenworth.com/locations/winter-locations/icicle-river\">\u003Cspan>Icicle River Trails\u003C/span>\u003C/a> are our beginner-friendly location with excellent scenery being tucked away at the mouth of the incredible Icicle Canyon. This is the default Nordic Lesson location.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Our&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https://skileavenworth.com/locations/winter-locations/golf-course\">\u003Cspan>Golf Course\u003C/span>\u003C/a> trail network boasts intermediate terrain tucked along the scenic Wenatchee River. Wide sweeping curves lead through open groves of huge pines while surrounded by gorgeous views of the Cascades and home to numerous deer that share the trails.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cspan>\u003Ca href=\"https://skileavenworth.com/locations/winter-locations/ski-hill\">Ski Hill\u003C/a>\u003C/span> is not only home to our alpine operations but also our more advanced Nordic trail system. These trails loop through beautiful forests and end back at the historic Ski Hill Lodge - the perfect place for apr&egrave;s-ski. This location also offers five kilometers of lighted Nordic skiing until 10pm every night during winter operations.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"https://skileavenworth.com/locations/winter-locations/peshastin-mill-site\">\u003Cspan>Peshastin Mill Site\u003C/span>\u003C/a> isn't groomed on as rigorous a schedule as the other locations, but we aim to get out there once a week. It offers about a 3/4 mile jaunt that is and dog friendly and not requiring of a ski ticket.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Washington","country":"USA","regions":["US-WA-LWSC"],"groups":[{"groupId":"GolfCourseNordic","groupName":"Nordic Trails","groupBounds":[[-120.6743618728681,47.57519217191352],[-120.66609773104842,47.58681881263798]]},{"groupId":"SnowshoeTrails","gr