/www.paysdesecrins.com/meteo-vallouise-pelvoux/"}},"elevation":1149,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2026-03-03T16:54:20.589Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"2"},{"clubId":"US-ID-HorseshoeCanyon","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"ID","permalink":"Horseshoe-Canyon","bounds":[[-111.3354502072184,43.71336767288837],[-111.30251121582896,43.74113731360941]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-11T18:52:03.517Z","weatherSources":["680907e6e3004a71b66ca6ca"],"name":{"en":"Horseshoe Canyon"},"city":{"en":"Driggs"},"groomedBy":{"en":"TVTAP"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-22c51b17-2562-42a3-9ea0-c68f755fefe5\">The groomed winter trail, if skied/ridden/walked in whole, is approximately 12km with 1000 feet of elevation gain and loss. The first mile of trail is a shared use access point with snowmachines, skiers, snowshoers, fat bikers, etc. The trails as an entity, an old forest roadbed, meanders in and out of mixed conifer and aspen forests and there is ample opportunity for\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-16a6a866-6281-4e57-841c-b516c0f4167f\">some hearty, sustained climbs. The area is also home to a wide array of birds and wildlife.&nbsp;\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-16a6a866-6281-4e57-841c-b516c0f4167f\">&nbsp;\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-16a6a866-6281-4e57-841c-b516c0f4167f\">\n\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-4c3c2cb1-c446-412d-b300-3c85e1785046\">At the trailhead there are two groomed routes. One road/trail to the north goes towards Packsaddle and the other to the northwest goes over Horseshoe Creek road bridge towards Sam. Take the trail to the northwest\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-bc350720-fee8-413e-b941-edc88fce62b2\">and towards Sam. This trail system is a combination of a shorter interior loop and one longer out and back trail. From the parking lot to the Horseshoe Canyon Yurt is 1.1 miles and about 400 feet of elevation gain. In the area of the Horseshoe Canyon Yurt, you will be rewarded with spectacular Teton and Big Hole views.&nbsp;\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv data-block-id=\"block-16a6a866-6281-4e57-841c-b516c0f4167f\">&nbsp;\u003C/div>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>Horseshoe Canyon is just about 11 miles west of Driggs, ID, and is accessed via the South Fork Horseshoe Trailhead. To access the groomed trails, park at the South Fork Horseshoe Trailhead.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Idaho","country":"USA","regions":["US-WY-JHNordic-TetonValleyTrails","US-WY-JHNordic","US-CCSAA"],"logo":"2023-04-04T21-53-25-289-07:00_US-WY-Driggs_logo.png","banner":"2025-03-13T16-22-50-769-07:00_US-ID-HorseshoeCanyon_Alexis_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"fourDaysAgo","active":true,"timezone":"America/Edmonton","liveTrack":true,"trackset":true,"tracksetType":"tracksetChecked","coordinates":[43.718942,-111.303514],"distance":9267.37473377955,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":9.27,"percent":100}],"links":{"weather":{"en":"https://www.yr.no/en/forecast/daily-table/43.719,-111.304"}},"sponsor":true,"sponsorLogo":"2023-04-04T21-53-25-289-07:00_US-WY-Driggs_logo.png","elevation":1977,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2025-02-13T19:46:18.836Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-25T20:30:28.316Z","clubId":"US-ID-HorseshoeCanyon","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>See y'all next winter 26/27.&nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"6543cbe9ec5650f1762f16b7","author":"Kevin E","timestamp":"2026-03-25T20:29:31.000Z","deviceId":"644ECA70-6191-4321-8A71-687502221959"}},{"clubId":"QC-NCC","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"CA","regionId":"QC","permalink":"NCC-Gatineau-Park","bounds":[[-76.09799458224946,45.439447916952844],[-75.75893240874669,45.641919984125934]],"offlineMapsBounds":[[[[-76.10313860198168,45.5904900654494],[-76.07727910429735,45.5904900654494],[-76.07727910429735,45.58639256794516],[-76.06085950470273,45.58639256794516],[-76.06085950470273,45.59386638155819],[-76.03635514698719,45.59386638155819],[-76.03635514698719,45.5964047