idge Project is underway. The Ketchum Ranger District and Wood River Trails Coalition report this week they will be doing a falling operation around the Fox Creek bridge site and starting in June crews will be mobilizing bridge materials along the first mile of Fox Creek trail to the bridge site and Titus Trails will be actively working in the Fox Creek area. Please be aware of equipment on the trail and be patient when encountering crews, be sure and give the crews a wide berth and make eye contact with equipment operators and follow their instructions when passing.&nbsp;\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>There will be occasional closures on the trailhead and trail while heavy equipment is working and materials are being transported. Please continue to check back for updates and more details.&nbsp;&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Tentative Closure dates:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>June 27-29: Trailhead and trail closure to fly in bridge materials.\u003C/p>"},"account":"65556e472cde45640d8a8ce6","author":"Ashley","timestamp":"2026-05-18T14:59:00.000Z"},{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.964Z","clubId":"US-ID-BCRDKetchumtoSNRA","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>\u003CspanCalibri',sans-serif;\">SNRA Head Quarters\u003C/span>\u003C/strong>\u003CspanCalibri',sans-serif;\"> will be open weekdays 8:30-4:30 June 15 -September 7\u003Csup>th\u003C/sup>. \u003C/span>\u003C/p>"},"account":"65556e472cde45640d8a8ce6","author":"Ashley","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:49:00.000Z"},{"updatedAt":"2026-07-11T15:49:56.964Z","clubId":"US-ID-BCRDKetchumtoSNRA","type":"grooming-report-notice","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Forest Service reports: A sheep band is grazing southwest of the fishing ponds in Lake Creek. They will continue to graze northwest towards the headwaters of Lake Creek. &nbsp; &nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"65556e472cde45640d8a8ce6","author":"Ashley","timestamp":"2026-07-09T01:58:00.000Z"}]},{"clubId":"US-ID-BCRDWarmSprings","seasonSwitch":"US-ID-BCRD","season":"summ