38533881049],[-95.21296532332538,49.69027651207979],[-95.20755040140955,49.69027651207979],[-95.20755040140955,49.6875338817848],[-95.19782972940392,49.6875338817848],[-95.19782972940392,49.682833190238384],[-95.15679823827983,49.682833190238384],[-95.15679823827983,49.695509692535566],[-95.14904685056212,49.695509692535566],[-95.14904685056212,49.705621832905976],[-95.15679823827983,49.705621832905976],[-95.15679823827983,49.71758639363825],[-95.19782972940392,49.71758639363825],[-95.19782972940392,49.71429639366249],[-95.19812739160334,49.71429639366249],[-95.19812739160334,49.71104343082963],[-95.20190947020215,49.71104343082963],[-95.20190947020215,49.710336393691655],[-95.20723332984689,49.710336393691655],[-95.20723332984689,49.708904610668974],[-95.20772336608107,49.708904610668974],[-95.20772336608107,49.70771989245564],[-95.21378124616244,49.70771989245564],[-95.21378124616244,49.70760742983775],[-95.21522498905786,49.70760742983775],[-95.21522498905786,49.70544239372769],[-95.22820124430312,49.70544239372769],[-95.22820124430312,49.693428190160425]]]],"lastGroomed":"2026-03-26T18:20:49.000Z","weatherSources":["68f973531dc30260c14050aa"],"name":{"en":"Falcon Ridge Ski Slopes"},"city":{"en":"Falcon Lake"},"groomedBy":{"en":"Falcon Ridge Ski Slopes"},"description":{"en":"\u003Cp>A lovable little ski resort tucked away in the woods, on the shores of beautiful Falcon Lake, Manitoba. The ski hill has 4 lifts for alpine skiing and snowboarding as well as a tubing lift. 12 runs and a vertical drop of 30m. A cozy, vintage chalet with a fully licensed cafe and restaurant. Equipment rentals for alpine skiing, snowboarding, tubing, Nordic skiing and snowshoeing. It is the perfect place for families and anyone looking for an introduction to alpine sports.\u003Cbr>\u003Cbr>The resort also maintains 25km of nordic ski trails groomed for skate and classic skiing, snowshoing and fat biking. Due to the rocky landscape, there is plenty of elevation change so skiers are recommended to have some experience before heading out on the trails. In summer, the resort maintains 25km of hiking and mountain biking trails that range from wide, gravel path style to technical single track. Again, Falcon Ridge is well known for its technicality on the trails so make sure you have some experience before heading out.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>The Owl Wing Cafe, located at the resort Welcom Centre is open 7 days a week and is the hub for all your trail needs. Come relax by the fire after your trail experience with a cold beer or hot coffee in your hand.&nbsp;\u003Cbr>\u003Cbr>Manitoba Park Pass required. Park passes can be purchased online at: https://www.manitobaelicensing.ca/licensing.page. There are no trail fees for using mountain bike, hike, cross country ski, snowshoe or fat bike trails. Note: Park entry is free for the 25/26 winter season.\u003Cbr>\u003Cbr>Know your limits. Trail users assume all risks. Conditions can change quickly out on the trails so please use caution, be prepared and ski within your abilities.\u003C/p>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cp>Falcon Trails Resort its located in Treaty 3, traditional lands of the Anishinabewaki,&nbsp;M&eacute;tis and&nbsp;Očeti &Scaron;ak&oacute;wiŋ (Sioux)&nbsp;people.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>You'll find us at the quiet south east end of Falcon Lake in Manitoba's Whiteshell Provincial Park, just off the #1 highway, a 90 minute drive east from Winnipeg, about 15 minutes west of the Manitoba/Ontario border.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Once you turn off the #1 Highway into Falcon Lake, take the South Shore Road along the south side of the lake (past the golf course and the lumber yard). We are located right at the end of the road, about a 15 minute drive from the highway.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Manitoba","country":"Canada","groups":[{"groupId":"NordicTrails","groupName":"Nordic Trails","groupBounds":[[-95.20966366862056,49.688796664403775],[-95.16334937023382,49.70673931203941]]},{"groupId":"FatbikeandSnowshoeTrails","groupOrder":1,"groupName":"Fatbike and Snowshoe Trails","groupBounds":[[-95.19739027553437,49.694360671315465],[-95.17808934999357,49.70744634918239]]},{"groupId":"RoadsandSnowmobile","groupOrder":2,"groupName":"Roads and Snowmobile","groupBounds":[[-95.22264004873546,49.6864306713178],[-95.15460900210545,49.71398931203727]]}],"logo":"2025-10-22T16-59-42-068-07:00_CA-MB-FalconRidgeSkiSlopes_logo_0.png","banner":"2025-10-22T16-57-42-074-07:00_CA-MB-FalconRidgeSkiSlopes_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"twoWeeksAgo","active":true,"timezone":"Canada/Central","liveTrack":true,"trackset":true,"tracksetType":"tracksetChecked","coordinates":[49.703832,-95.190746],"distance":30926.973125763805,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":15.79,"percent":51.05094851207369},{"id":"intermediate","distance":6.86,"percent":22.192520238443844},{"id":"advanced","distance":5.48,"percent":17.727731420079028}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.falconridgeski.com/"},"weather":{"en":"https://www.yr.no/en/forecast/daily-table/49.704,%20-95.191"}},"snowDepthUnpacked":20,"snow12h":5,"snow24h":15,"snowAnnual":20,"currentCond":"marginal, rock skis recommended","elevation":332,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2026-01-23T00:20:32.844Z","tempUnits":"C","timezoneUTC":"-5","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-04-10T16:51:50.919Z","clubId":"CA-MB-FalconRidgeSkiSlopes","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>Heygoodmornin!&nbsp;\u003Cbr>Spring has taken a mighty but slow grip and as a result the cross country ski season are officially closed for the season. \u003Cbr>The trails do remain open to hiking/ biking year round as well as the Owl Wing Cafe is open daily 9:30am-4:30pm.&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Ski you next winter!\u003C/p>"},"account":"68fc24ba9b6ea1cd0b688ca5","author":"Ryan The Groomer ","timestamp":"2026-04-10T16:49:16.230Z"}},{"clubId":"US-WY-NortheastSkiTrails","season":"winter","activities":["nordic"],"countryId":"US","regionId":"WY","permalink":"Northeast-Ski-Trails","bounds":[[-110.0840932796260