pect Mountain maintains more than 30&nbsp;kilometers of trails. When the snow falls, the trails are expertly groomed for both skating and classical cross-country skiing. Most trails have tracks set on either side with a wide skating lane in the center. There are also special snowshoeing and single-track&nbsp;trails. We have trails&nbsp;from beginner to expert. The&nbsp;Mountain Trail is popular with experts looking to climb more than 400 feet to&nbsp;the top of the mountain. After enjoying the view into the valley below, get ready for several kilometers of downhill fun!\u003Cbr>Prospect welcomes skiers who want to skin up the mountain and ski down the former alpine trails with a vertical drop of 610 feet. Even though you are not using the cross country trails, \u003Cem>\u003Cstrong>you need to buy \u003C/strong>\u003C/em>a day pass. This helps us support the plowing of the parking lot and mowing those downhill trails in the off season.\u003Cbr>Private and semi-private lessons are available by appointment. Call (802)442-2575.\u003Cbr>Since 2018 Prospect Mountain has been managed by the Prospect Mountain Association (PMA), a not-for-profit 501(c)3 made up of volunteer \u003Cem>\u003Cstrong>who\u003C/strong>\u003C/em> help steer the future of Prospect.\u003C/p>"},"region":"Vermont","country":"USA","regions":["US-VT-SkiVT"],"groups":[{"groupId":"Snowmaking","groupName":"Practice Slope","groupBounds":[[-73.07900107324784,42.87293067308378],[-73.07544280291884,42.87627359401894]]},{"groupId":"GroomedTrails","groupOrder":1,"groupName":"Groomed Nordic Trails","groupBounds":[[-73.09677694195814,42.86344067308598],[-73.05896266158233,42.883379313808994]]},{"groupId":"BackcountryTrails","groupOrder":2,"groupName":"Backcountry Nordic Trails","groupBounds":[[-73.09600839949599,42.86014067308672],[-73.06243269520203,42.881689313809396]]},{"groupId":"Snowshoe","groupOrder":3,"groupName":"Snowshoe Trails","groupBounds":[[-73.08071389214108,42.87159443317729],[-73.06386578639423,42.