end in April.&nbsp;\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Enjoy over 27 kilometers of set track and wide skate lanes on a&nbsp;groomed trail system&nbsp;that offers ample terrain for every style and ability level.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>From our well-stocked rental program, select classic XC skis, skate skis, fat bikes, or snowshoes. Not sure what you need? No problem! Our friendly staff will guide you on &ldquo;all things Nordic,&rdquo; and lessons are certainly a good place to start- see ya out there!\u003C/p>"},"descriptionDirections":{"en":"\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Ch3>WARNING:\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>DO&nbsp;NOT&nbsp;USE GPS DIRECTIONS if they ask you take County Road 18 or 19 at any point. These are 4X4 roads in the summer and closed to motor traffic in the winter. Those directions are incorrect,&nbsp;and you may get lost or stuck.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please use the Google Map&nbsp;above and choose &ldquo;Directions,&rdquo;&nbsp;or&nbsp;call us at&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"tel: 7194868114\">719.486.8114\u003C/a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;\u003Ca href=\"tel: 7194861750\">719.486.1750\u003C/a>&nbsp;to speak directly to our staff to get accurate directions. They are also printed below from any direction you may be coming from.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Cdiv>\n\u003Ch3>From Vail / Minturn, CO\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>(From I-70), Take&nbsp;exit 171&nbsp;to merge onto&nbsp;Highway 24-E/US-6E.&nbsp;&nbsp;Continue on&nbsp;Highway 24-E&nbsp;for approximately 29 miles to the top of Tennessee Pass/Continental Divide and turn left at the large&nbsp;Tennessee Pass Nordic Center/Ski Cooper entrance sign. Proceed up the access road to find the&nbsp;Tennessee Pass Nordic Center&nbsp;on the right side of the parking lot.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3>From Leadville, CO\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Travel north on&nbsp;Highway 24-W&nbsp;approximately 9 miles to the top of Tennessee Pass/Continental Divide and turn right at the large&nbsp;Tennessee Pass Nordic Center/Ski Cooper entrance sign. Proceed up the access road to find the&nbsp;Tennessee Pass Nordic Center&nbsp;on the right side of the parking lot.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch3>From Denver, CO\u003C/h3>\n\u003Cp>Travel west on Interstate 70 approximately 80 miles and take exit 195 to merge onto CO-91 Stoward Copper Mountain/Leadville.&nbsp;&nbsp;Proceed on CO-91 S approximately 22 miles and turn right onto US-24 W (just before entering Leadville, CO).&nbsp; Proceed on US-24 W approximately 8 miles to the top of Tennessee Pass/Continental Divide and turn right at the large Tennessee Pass Nordic Center/Ski Cooper entrance sign. Proceed up the access road to find the Tennessee Pass Nordic Center on the right side of the parking.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003C/div>"},"region":"Colorado","country":"USA","logo":"2026-03-01T18-07-20-416-08:00_US-CO-TennesseePassNordicCenter_0.jpg","banner":"2025-12-15T18-42-54-588-08:00_US-CO-TennesseePassNordicCenter_0.jpg","lastGroomedClass":"oneDayAgo","active":true,"timezone":"US/Mountain","liveTrack":true,"trackset":true,"coordinates":[39.360618,-106.302989],"distance":24497.759874441803,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":16.87,"percent":68.86704233835846},{"id":"intermediate","distance":6.01,"percent":24.533362048641944},{"id":"advanced","distance":1.62,"percent":6.599595612999624}],"links":{"website":{"en":"https://www.tennesseepass.com"},"weather":{"en":"https://www.wunderground.com/weather/us/co/leadville/80461"},"phone":{"en":"719.486.1750"},"ig":{"en":"https://www.instagram.com/TennPassCO/"}},"elevation":3215,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2026-03-20T21:07:02.670Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-22T22:02:43.863Z","clubId":"US-CO-TennesseePassNordicCenter","type":"grooming-report","content":{"en":"\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Nordic Trails Closed\u003C/strong> due to recent and rapid melt.&nbsp;\u003C/p>"},"account":"69a08e79602fa3e8b55ec97a","author":"Daniel","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:00:58.000Z","deviceId":"7E4E2569-A5D5-4FE1-8048-D0191A4FD50B"}},{"clubId":"FR-IS-SiteNordiqueDe