otorized use with the exception of the Skyline Drive Trail. All of the trails are groomed and maintained with county funding via the Sublette County Recreation Board, and with extensive volunteer support and there is no fee for use. While recreating on these trails, please respect the courtesy rules (detailed below). Enjoy and we look forward to seeing you out there!\u003C/p>"},"region":"Wyoming","country":"USA","lastGroomedClass":"not-groomed","active":true,"timezone":"US/Mountain","liveTrack":true,"coordinates":[42.963385,-109.767878],"distance":42570.163408591296,"distanceGroups":[{"id":"easy","distance":13.21,"percent":31.042408045641075},{"id":"intermediate","distance":25.07,"percent":58.90159599088006},{"id":"advanced","distance":4.28,"percent":10.055995963478843}],"elevation":2532,"lastTrailsUpdate":"2026-06-24T22:41:09.730Z","tempUnits":"F","timezoneUTC":"-6","reportLatest":{"type":"grooming-report"}}],"headers":{"date":["Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:36:27 GMT"],"content-type":["application/json; charset=utf-8"],"content-length":["1896661"],"connection":["keep-alive"],"server":["cloudflare"],"nel":["{\"report_to\":\"cf-nel\",\"success_fraction\":0.0,\"max_age\":604800}"],"x-powered-by":["Express"],"vary":["Origin"],"access-control-allow-credentials":["true"],"etag":["W/\"1cf0d5-RFYCv/vZESOS0JzUXQ/M7erYu8s\""],"cf-cache-status":["DYNAMIC"],"report-to":["{\"group\":\"cf-nel\",\"max_age\":604800,\"endpoints\":[{\"url\":\"https://a.nel.cloudflare.com/report/v4?s=5r3fgIVri4ECxx2p9oYqbxPjEwxgb0Yv36cnAWzX4AoaKQgQDWFWN%2FtM0zz9H0V8u%2B9PAeOnA8tolcCuD2KZQHjJEhcdKF0ibHAX31qpzBAXIt1%2Bh1nZK3uWeL9EY7RSzvC9RmjZvw%3D%3D\"}]}"],"cf-ray":["a1ac7404bcbc1693-YYZ"]},"status":200,"statusText":"OK","url":"https://api2.nordic-pulse.com/v3/ski-areas-npww","responseType":"json"},"4091552638":{"body":[{"_id":"65ebae73c226cb73efd13596","updatedAt":"2022-03-13T23:41:03.448Z","name":{"en":"Sovereign2SilverStar Ski Marathon"},"city":"Vernon","clubId":["BC-SovereignLake","BC-Silverstar"],"permalink":"Sovereign-2-SilverStar","region":"British Columbia","regionId":"BC","country":"Canada","countryId":"CA","network":"BC-SovereignLake.geojson","logo":"BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png","banner":"BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-banner.jpg","website":"https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/","active":true,"timezone":"America/Vancouver","liveTrack":true,"dist":true,"groomers":[],"coordinates":[50.364782,-119.1078138],"tabs":[{"name":"Overview","content":"\u003Ca href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg style='float:left;max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Cp>The Sovereign 2 SilverStar Ski Marathon is back for it’s 3rd year.  This is a \u003Cb>point to party\u003C/b> event with two of everything: two days (classic and skate), two distances each day (40km and 21km), and two ski areas (start at Sovereign Lake and finish on Main Street of SilverStar village)..\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Finishing is Winning: After the ‘competitive’ waves start, the smaller ‘fun’ waves will be spaced out to allow everyone to enjoy their time on the trails. With the largest daily groomed network of Nordic trails in Canada, there are no laps or repeated trail sections, just a lot of scenery.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>The two areas provide an adventure that carries on well after the skiing is done. When you get to the finish line you're just getting started as the party gets underway at the great local restaurants and bars.\u003C/p>"},{"name":"Schedule","content":"\u003Cp>\u003Cb>April 6th, 2024:\u003C/b> Classic Day: your choice of 42km or 21km.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cb>April 7th, 2024:\u003C/b> Free/Skate Day: your choice of 42km or 21km.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Start in a World Cup stadium at Sovereign Lake, finish on Main Street in SilverStar village.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Stop at a food station, take pictures at the viewpoints, experience the trails with small wave starts to allow more room to appreciate the scenery.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Build your own experience: choose between competitive and fun waves, ride the gondola on a sunny afternoon, add a multisport experience 20 minutes drive to the valley below.\u003C/p>"},{"name":"Registration","content":"\u003Cp>\u003Cb>Registration deadline is 6pm on March 31.\u003C/b>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>You can register for one day or both days, and you can ski either two long distances or two short distances or mix or match!  Skiers who register for both days get a $15 credit for the second event.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Refund Policy: Please refer to the registration page for the refund policy.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Ca class='button' href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/registration' target='_blank'>Registration Info\u003C/a>"},{"name":"Organizers","content":"\u003Cp>Sovereign2Silver Star Ski Marathon is hosted by Sovereign Lake Nordic Centre and Silver Star Mountain Resort.\u003C/p>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Ca href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/' target'_blank'>Sovereign2SilverStar.com\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Ca href='https://sovereignlake.com' target='_blank'>SovereignLake.com\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Ca href='https://www.skisilverstar.com/events/sovereign-2-silverstar/' target='_blank'>SkiSilverStar.com\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003Cdiv class='logos-wrap'>\u003Ca href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/' target'_blank'>\u003Cimg style='max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Ca href='https://sovereignlake.com' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-SovereignLake.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Ca href='https://www.skisilverstar.com/events/sovereign-2-silverstar/' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg style='max-height:100px;' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-SilverStar.png' />\u003C/a>\u003C/div>"}],"eventId":"s2s","eventStart":"2024-04-06T17:52:16.770Z","eventEnd":"2024-04-07T17:52:16.770Z","eventCategories":["Loppet","Ski Marathon"],"eventNotice":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1klDroD4YuGtXTXdCbdBG1x04eyCSiDqB/view?usp=sharing"},{"_id":"622e998fd2ecccdd0e6cf610","updatedAt":"2022-03-13T23:41:03.448Z","name":{"en":"Sovereign2SilverStar Ski Marathon"},"city":"Vernon","clubId":[],"permalink":"Sovereign-2-SilverStar","region":"British Columbia","regionId":"BC","country":"Canada","countryId":"CA","network":"BC-SovereignLake.geojson","logo":"BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png","banner":"BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-banner.jpg","website":"https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/","active":true,"timezone":"America/Vancouver","liveTrack":true,"dist":true,"groomers":[],"coordinates":[50.364782,-119.1078138],"tabs":[{"name":"Overview","content":"\u003Ca href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/' target'_blank'>\u003Cimg style='float:left;max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Cp>Sovereign Lake NC and SilverStar Mountain Resort are teaming up to present the Sovereign2SilverStar Ski Marathon. A \u003Cb>point to party\u003C/b> event with two of everything: two days (classic and skate), two distances each day (40km and 21km), and two ski areas (start at Sovereign Lake and finish on Main Street of SilverStar village).\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Finishing is Winning: After the ‘competitive’ waves start, the smaller ‘fun’ waves will be spaced out to allow everyone to enjoy their time on the trails. With the largest daily groomed network of Nordic trails in Canada, there are no laps or repeated trail sections, just a lot of scenery.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>The two areas are working together to build an adventure that carries on well after the skiing is done. When you get to the finish line you're just getting started as the party gets underway at the great local restaurants and bars.\u003C/p>"},{"name":"Schedule","content":"\u003Cp>\u003Cb>April 1st, 2023:\u003C/b> Classic Day: your choice of 42km or 21km.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cb>April 2nd, 2023:\u003C/b> Free/Skate Day: your choice of 42km or 21km.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Start in a World Cup stadium at Sovereign Lake, finish on Main Street in SilverStar village.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Stop at a food station, take pictures at the viewpoints, experience the trails with small wave starts to allow more room to appreciate the scenery.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Build your own experience: choose between competitive and fun waves, ride the gondola on a sunny afternoon, add a multisport experience 20 minutes drive to the valley below.\u003C/p>"},{"name":"Registration","content":"\u003Cp>\u003Cb>Registration deadline is 8pm on March 27th.\u003C/b>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>You can register for one day or both days, and you can ski either two long distances or two short distances or mix or match!  Skiers who register for both days get a $15 credit for the second event.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Refund Policy: Refunds are available only in the case of the cancellation of the S2S Ski Marathon event. If the event is cancelled, a refund of your registration fee less an administration charge (based on costs to that date) will be made to you.registration content\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Ca class='button' href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/registration' target='_blank'>Registration Info\u003C/a>"},{"name":"Organizers","content":"\u003Cp>Sovereign2Silver Star Ski Marathon is hosted by Sovereign Lake Nordic Centre and Silver Star Mountain Resort.\u003C/p>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Ca href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/' target'_blank'>Sovereign2SilverStar.com\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Ca href='https://sovereignlake.com' target='_blank'>SovereignLake.com\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Ca href='https://www.skisilverstar.com/events/sovereign-2-silverstar/' target='_blank'>SkiSilverStar.com\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003Cdiv class='logos-wrap'>\u003Ca href='https://www.sovereign2silverstar.com/' target'_blank'>\u003Cimg style='max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Ca href='https://sovereignlake.com' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-SovereignLake.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Ca href='https://www.skisilverstar.com/events/sovereign-2-silverstar/' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg style='max-height:100px;' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-SilverStar.png' />\u003C/a>\u003C/div>"}],"eventId":"s2s2023","eventStart":"2023-04-01T17:52:16.770Z","eventEnd":"2023-04-02T17:52:16.770Z","eventCategories":["Loppet","Ski Marathon"],"eventNotice":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1WFW-uH-c8WG9WwyUcqKpO686q93PoltD/view"},{"_id":"63792813b99682198ced397b","updatedAt":"2022-03-13T23:41:03.448Z","name":{"en":"2023 World Junior Championships"},"city":"Callaghan Valley/Whistler","clubId":"BC-CallaghanValley","permalink":"2023-World-Juniors","region":"British Columbia","regionId":"BC","regionsData":[""],"country":"Canada","countryId":"CA","network":"BC-SovereignLake.geojson","groups":[],"logo":"2022-11-19T11-04-52-411-08:00_BC-CallaghanValley_logo-200.png","banner":"2022-11-19T11-06-31-079-08:00_BC-CallaghanValley_Julien.jpg","website":"https://wjc2023.ca/","website_fr":"","active":true,"timezone":"America/Vancouver","liveTrack":true,"trackset":false,"tracksetType":"","dist":true,"groomers":[],"coordinates":[50.1379878,-123.1253489],"photoCred":"","photoCredUrl":"","apiAccess":["99kRFt5LIzKQ"],"tabs":[{"name":"Overview","content":"\u003Ca href='https://wjc2023.ca/' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg class='event-logo ski-nats' style='float:left;max-height:130px' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/uploads/2022-11-19T11-04-52-411-08:00_BC-CallaghanValley_logo-200.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Cp>The FIS Nordic Junior World Ski Championships is organized for the top 16 to 20 year old Cross-Country Skiing, Ski Jumping and Nordic Combined athletes in the World, and the U23 Cross Country World Ski Championships is for the best 21 to 23 year old Cross-Country Skiing athletes.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>The Black Tusk Nordic Events Society is the organizing committee in charge of planning, financing and executing the events. \u003C/p>"}],"eventId":"wjc23","eventStart":"2023-01-27T17:52:16.770Z","eventEnd":"2023-02-05T17:52:16.770Z","eventCategories":["Competition"],"mainLink":"https://www.wjc2023.ca/livestream/","mainLinkName":"Live Stream"},{"_id":"623cf22c6797517169bcf4a6","name":{"en":"La Classique Alex Harvey"},"city":"Saint Ferréol les Neiges","clubId":"QC-Mont-Sainte-Anne","permalink":"Classique-Alex-Harvey","region":"Quebec","regionId":"QC","country":"Canada","countryId":"CA","network":"BC-SovereignLake.geojson","logo":"BC-Sovereign2SilverStar-logo.png","banner":"QC-MSA-AlexHarveyClassique-banner.jpg","website":"http://www.cneph.ca/classique-alex-harvey.html","timezone":"America/Vancouver","groomers":[],"coordinates":[47.1228269,-70.875676],"tabs":[{"name":"Aperçu","content":"\u003Ca href='http://www.cneph.ca/classique-alex-harvey.html' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg style='float:left;max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/QC-MSA-AlexHarveyClassique-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Cp>Participez à la Classique Alex Harvey, organisée par le CNEPH\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Les surplus de l'évènement serviront à supporter le développement de l’excellence en ski de fond !\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Dimanche le 3 avril 2022, au Centre de ski de fond – Mont-Sainte-Anne, Saint-Ferréol-les-Neiges\u003Cbr />Parcours de 25 km et 50 km (technique libre) sur le réseau du Centre de ski de fond Mont-Sainte-Anne\u003Cbr />Inscription jusqu’au 27 mars 2022 - Le nombre de participants est limité à 400.\u003Cbr />Cocktail avec les athlètes du CNEPH le samedi 2 avril\u003Cbr />\u003C/p>"},{"name":"En Savoir Plus","content":"\u003Ch6>Date & Lieu\u003C/h6>\u003Cp>Dimanche 3 avril 2022\u003Cbr />Centre de ski de fond – Mont-Sainte-Anne, Saint-Ferréol-les-Neiges\u003C/p?>\u003Ch6>Épreuves\u003C/h6>\u003Cp>25 km et 50 km – Style Pas de patin\u003C/p>\u003Ch6>Accès au site – navette\u003C/h6>\u003Cp>L’accès au site est réservé aux participants et se fera en autobus à partir du stationnement P2, situé 500 mètres à l’est de la station de ski alpin. Consultez le «Guide du participant» pour plus de détails.\u003C/p>\u003Ch6>Guide du participant\u003C/h6>\u003Ca href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1FzyStSbfV2RA3ZB7IZkmSaP4xQZaYcze/view?usp=sharing' target='_blank'>Télécharger le guide du participant\u003C/a>\u003Cbr />\u003Ca href='https://drive.google.com/file/d/1H-m_cSY_cwBW_ige1dWFb3LBS4Gve-qT/view?usp=sharing' target='_blank'>Download the participant guide\u003C/a>"},{"name":"Inscription","content":"\u003Cp>Inscription en ligne sur zone4.ca jusqu'au 27 mars 2022.\u003Cbr/>Notez que le nombre de participants est limité à 400.\u003Cbr/>Numéro de licence annuelle SFQ requise ou licence d’événement (3$ non inclus)\u003Cbr/>Frais de Zone4/Carte de crédit en sus (sera ajouté à l’étape du paiement)\u003C/p>\u003Ca class='button' href='https://zone4.ca/register.asp?id=25913&lan=1' target='_blank'>Inscription\u003C/a>"},{"name":"Les Organisateurs","content":"\u003Cdiv class='logos-wrap'>\u003Ca href='http://www.cneph.ca/classique-alex-harvey.html' target'_blank'>\u003Cimg style='float:left;max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/QC-MSA-AlexHarveyClassique-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Ca href='http://www.cneph.ca/classique-alex-harvey.html' target'_blank'>\u003Cimg style='float:left;max-height:130px' class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/QC-MSA-CNEPH-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003C/div>"}],"eventId":"AHC22","eventStart":"2022-04-03T17:52:16.770Z","eventEnd":"2022-04-03T17:52:16.770Z","eventCategories":["Loppet"],"eventNotice":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1FzyStSbfV2RA3ZB7IZkmSaP4xQZaYcze/view"},{"_id":"6236c6b967975171694d7dda","updatedAt":"2022-03-13T23:41:03.448Z","name":{"en":"2022 Canadian Ski Championships & Super Tour Finals"},"city":"Callaghan Valley/Whistler","clubId":"BC-CallaghanValley","permalink":"2022-Ski-Nationals-Super-Tour-Finals","region":"British Columbia","regionId":"BC","regionsData":[""],"country":"Canada","countryId":"CA","regions":["Okanagan"],"network":"BC-SovereignLake.geojson","groups":[],"logo":"BC-SkiNationals2022-logo.png","banner":"BC-SkiNationals2022-banner.jpg","website":"https://skinationals2022.ca/","website_fr":"","active":true,"timezone":"America/Vancouver","liveTrack":true,"trackset":false,"tracksetType":"","dist":true,"groomers":[],"coordinates":[50.1379878,-123.1253489],"photoCred":"","photoCredUrl":"","distance":"47740.63539233763","distanceGroups":[],"inProgress":true,"inProgressExpiry":"2022-02-21T17:00:20.986Z","inProgressDate":"2022-02-21T14:00:20.986Z","apiAccess":["99kRFt5LIzKQ"],"tabs":[{"name":"Overview","content":"\u003Ca href='https://skinationals2022.ca/' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg class='event-logo ski-nats' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-SkiNationals2022-logo.png' />\u003C/a>\u003Cp>The Black Tusk Nordic Events Society (BTNES) wishes all participants welcome to Whistler/Squamish and the Whistler Olympic Park in March, 2022.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>The Canadian Cross-Country National Championship expects one of the largest gathering of the most talented skiers from both Canada and USA in the recent years. Combining the Championship with the US SuperTour finals will result in fierce competitions between US and Canadian skiers coming from the 2022 Beijing Olympic Games and the final World Cup races, and the domestic skiers being ready to showcase their talents.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>The Junior and U23 eligible skiers will be able to test out the courses that will be used for next year’s Junior- and U23 World Nordic & Cross-Country Championships\u003C/p>\u003Cdiv>\u003C/div>"},{"name":"Schedule","content":"\u003Cb>Mar 20\u003C/b> - Interval start FR (all) + ParaNordic Short Distance \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 21\u003C/b> - Interval start CL (all) + ParaNordic Middle distance \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 22\u003C/b> - Official training (for sprint) \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 23\u003C/b> - Long sprint CL (U20 – Sen) + ParaNordic sprint \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 24\u003C/b> - Short sprint CL (U16, U18) \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 25\u003C/b> - Team sprint FR \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 26\u003C/b> - Official training Mass-start / Festival Day \u003Cbr />\u003Cb>Mar 27\u003C/b> - Long Mass-start FR (U20 – Senior) / Short Mass-start FR (U16, U18) \u003Cbr />\u003Cp>\u003Ca href='https://skinationals2022.ca/race-info/schedule/' target='_blank'>Full Schedule\u003C/a>\u003C/p>"},{"name":"Organizers","content":"\u003Cp>\u003Ca href='https://blacktusknordic.com/' target='_blank'>\u003Cimg class='event-logo' src='https://api.nordic-pulse.com/static/images/BC-BlackTuskNordic-logo.png' />\u003C/a>The 2022 Canadian Ski Championships & Super Tour Finals is organized by the Black Tusk Nordic Events Society. BTNES hosts high-level Nordic events with a focus on encouraging sport excellence to the World Championship and Olympic levels. We are committed to fostering community and driving economic opportunities for Nordic Sports in the Sea to Sky corridor. Between now and 2023 we will host a variety of events in preparation for the World Junior Championships.\u003C/p>"}],"eventId":"skiNats22","eventStart":"2022-03-20T17:52:16.770Z","eventEnd":"2022-03-27T17:52:16.770Z","eventCategories":["Competition"],"mainLink":"https://skinationals2022.ca/live-stream/","mainLinkName":"Live Stream","mainLinkTwo":"https://zone4.ca/event/2022/3E7AEA5A/","mainLinkTwoName":"Results","eventNotice":"https://skinationals2022.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Final-2022_Nationals_EN_R2.pdf"}],"headers":{"date":["Tue, 14 Jul 2026 00:36:27 GMT"],"content-type":["application/json; charset=utf-8"],"content-length":["16977"],"connection":["keep-alive"],"server":["clo